reviews.text: We didn't have time to do a tour unfortunately but Terry and Beth made sure our experience was outstanding. Terry talked to us all about the distillery and her family's connections while Beth got us a tasting together so we could try a few different things. Both ladies and Terry's niece (I'm sorry I can't remember your name!) were so warm, friendly and welcoming it made a huge impact on our day. We will definitely be going back when the weather is nicer!

This bourbon distillery tour is the BEST tour you'll go on and here's why: 1) Tour guide, Rick K 2) So much amazing and rich history 3) The decadent bourbon (by far the best tasting AND the best price!) 4) The tour is free!!!  5) You absolutely can go there just to taste the bourbon! 6) You can sit on the patio and listen to live music. This is a distillery is a MUST!!
Long drive but we'll worth it!  Incredible tour and tour guides.  A nice selection of items in gift shop. And a nice selection from the distilliers.  Would definitely go back.
This is one of the best bourbon tours in Kentucky! Our tour guide Rick was very good. Great setup, very knowledgeable tour guides. We had a blast last night! I highly recommend this spot!

We visited and toured in September this year.  Katie showed us around, and she was great!!  Lots of history combined with bourbon making facts.  She made the day for us!  The tasting was great with Old Barton and 1792.  We left with bourbon glasses and three bottles..  Great!

What a beautiful location! It's a scenic wonder and the employees here are.so friendly and welcoming. We had a tour from Laura and she was friendly, engaging and so hysterical. It was a very interactive tour we loved every bit of it. The bottle dipping at the end was great also. 
The restaurant had very delicious food and great alcohol beverages.

Loved this tour. The grounds are absolutely stunning and I would argue the most beautiful distillery I've seen yet. Loved the tour and our guide. The restaurant has some disappointing hours (closes ~2:30pm), but that was our fault for setting up an afternoon tour. And of course, being able to dip our bottles in the signature red wax was the highlight of the trip!

What a wonderful experience. I can’t say enough great things about this place. Even though I was “late” to attend my barrel aging ceremony (meaning I missed it) they still put my name on a bottle and let me dip it in hot wax. Thank you so much for your hospitality! We will be back soon.

Our third stop on the Kentucky Bourbon Trail and one of the most memorable! Not only was our tour guide Chaz friendly and knowledgeable, the tour itself was fun and the tasting at the end was the best of the whole trip. Give yourself two hours minimum here, you're going to want to stay even after the 90 minute tour. The grounds are beautiful and the tour itself is pretty interactive and takes you throughout the entire process. We even got a good lunch right there on property at Star Hill. Don't miss this tour if you're on the Kentucky Bourbon Trail!

This was an awesome tour and an amazing experience to learn all about some of the best bourbon in the land! Our tour guide was knowledgeable and informative and provided an amazing experience for my group. History behind this place is quite awesome. They are also very military friendly I'm patriotic. I had a great time dipping my own bottle in the gift shop after the tour was over.
Loved the facilities and the atmosphere

We have our annual Girl Trip here. We stay 
All weekend here. We bring air mattresses and spend the night here. It's cool
Great history and beautiful architecture. A mist see!
Very clean, looks to offer wonderful service. Nice people. Sounds great.
Pretty cool old house
Plenty of room inside and out. Nice to see the old home and craftsmanship. Plus plenty of parking.

Awesome place to go to.
We are from out of town and spent most of our day here...
Great to see the old engine's
The North Pole Express was really fun with a surprise visit from Santa himself. The cookies and hot chocolate were good and we even got a pin! Fun for all ages. Wear you matching PJ's.
Nice outing with the family but could have been a little more exciting.
Great, scenic location with alot of railroad history on display. Friendly, informative staff.

We had an amazing time on the train robbery Sunday. I am go glad me and the kids were able to experience this. This was our first time riding on a real train and we all enjoyed it. I would definitely recommend this event to everyone. The tickets are a little pricey but well worth the spend.

Visiting this museum is a must when you are in Bardstown. The director, Linda, gave us an enlightened tour. The whole experience was as wonderful as we expected. Every piece in exhibition reflects the history of Whiskey and the building well. I would recommend this place to everyone.

This place was gold if you are a history buff! The ladies there enjoy what they do and make the experience that much better. They are very knowledgeable and friendly. The museum itself has a lot of cool artifacts and a fun history of its own. Defiantly a must see while on the Bourbon Trail.
If you haven't been here lately this museum has a new director who has been updating what's on display.  Its a great spot to learn about Bourbon, Prohibition, and local distilleries.

A good self guided tour of many times containing a good variety of Bourbon related historical artifacts and pictures.  It also has some war memorial items and artifacts from the time the building was a college.
Pretty cool place. I especially loved the displays with the old dusties.
One of my must-shop spots in Bardstown every time I go!! I always find something to buy at Barbara's!!
Beautiful decor and friendly service

The service was amazing, our waitress made sure our table was clean and we got our drinks super fast. The salad bar was really fresh. They had chicken nuggets and spaghetti for those picky eaters. The pizza bar had lots of various pizzas and it was hot. The food was excellent. They also have really good dessert that goes with the buffet.  This place is great if the whole family that wants different things. Family friendly place with great prices.

Cute joint with really friendly staff. Food was absolutely amazing and it came out quick. Really good kids menu as well and they served my daughter first which is always a plus. Definitely a place I will come back to!
Amazing pizza and the bread used for chicken parm sandwich is delicious.  I'm used to pizza from the northeast and don't like a lot of Louisville pizza places.  But this place is very good!
Pizza is consistently good. Never deviates. You know exactly what it's going to taste like every time. Would like better parking though.

I had a hankering for pizza for a week or so, I saw that all the local Bearno's were doing a fundraiser for the officer that passed away.  I stopped in about a half hour before close.  They had been extremely busy due to the public's support for the officer so they had run out of pizza, which is a good problem to have.   Unfortunately I had already paid for my pizza, they offered to exchange my pizza for sandwiches and wings, but I was craving delicious pizza.  I suggested getting a pizza tomorrow and they immediately agreed to that arrangement.  So tonight, I went in and had a nice conversation with one of the team members about our mutual love of Darth Vader, got my pizza and I could not be happier.
